Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

Erno, that's not the correct usage for DocImpact, which should be used to mark the change impacts documentation (like a new option). Have a read of https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Documentation/DocImpact

Olena: This is good information to have in the help text. Could you also add it to the declaration of the option in glance/registry/client/__init__.py? That way it will also be seen if the configuration file is auto generated. Thanks!

Patch Set 2:

Louis, I think it's exactly what is expected:

be it an added/altered/removed command line option, a deprecated or new feature, a caveat, _if you've written docs in the patch_, or if you're just not sure, just add "DocImpact" to a line in your commit message.

So yes I'm still expecting seeing the DocImpact flag in the commit message so that the Docs teams gets heads up that our in-repo documentation has  changed.
